			<h3 ><a href="#p1732613">Re: Cheap Razors</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=1732613&amp;sid=e801c7446165e76c4134a839dcb712e1#p1732613"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=39496&amp;sid=e801c7446165e76c4134a839dcb712e1">jay22</a></strong> &raquo; Tue Jun 25, 2013 9:24 am </p>

			

			<div class="content">FWIW, after using the mach 3 for 5-6 years, I recently switched to old school shaving using a DE razor and I have to say I am very, very satisfied. The shave is much better and it causes way less irritation to my face. I am able to get 10 shaves out of one blade, and one blade is about 30-40 cents. The shave itself is at least 5 times better than what I got from mach 3.</div>

			

		</div>

		
