			<h3 ><a href="#p1763313">Re: Cheap Razors</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=1763313&amp;sid=e801c7446165e76c4134a839dcb712e1#p1763313"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=23728&amp;sid=e801c7446165e76c4134a839dcb712e1">interplanetjanet</a></strong> &raquo; Tue Jul 30, 2013 5:03 am </p>

			

			<div class="content">Probably not applicable for the guys, but I gave up on shaving my legs many years ago when I found my first well-made epilator (a tweezer-style Braun, not those Epilady rotating spring torture devices).  There's no incremental cost at all and I can use it once every other week instead of shaving once every other day.<br /><br />The first time really hurts.  The second time kind of hurts.  After that it's not bad at all (the new hairs coming in are all thin with small roots).</div>

			

		</div>

		
